      • sk_canvas_destroy

        public static void sk_canvas_destroy(Skia.sk_canvas_t arg0)

      • sk_canvas_save

        public static int sk_canvas_save(Skia.sk_canvas_t arg0)
        Save the current matrix and clip on the canvas. When the balancing call to sk_canvas_restore() is made, the previous matrix and clip are restored.

      • sk_canvas_save_layer

        public static int sk_canvas_save_layer(Skia.sk_canvas_t arg0,
                                       @Const
                                       Skia.sk_rect_t arg1,
                                       @Const
                                       Skia.sk_paint_t arg2)
        This behaves the same as sk_canvas_save(), but in addition it allocates an offscreen surface. All drawing calls are directed there, and only when the balancing call to sk_canvas_restore() is made is that offscreen transfered to the canvas (or the previous layer).

        Parameters:
        sk_rect_t* - (may be null) This rect, if non-null, is used as a hint to limit the size of the offscreen, and thus drawing may be clipped to it, though that clipping is not guaranteed to happen. If exact clipping is desired, use sk_canvas_clip_rect().
        sk_paint_t* - (may be null) The paint is copied, and is applied to the offscreen when sk_canvas_restore() is called.

      • sk_canvas_restore

        public static void sk_canvas_restore(Skia.sk_canvas_t arg0)
        This call balances a previous call to sk_canvas_save() or sk_canvas_save_layer(), and is used to remove all modifications to the matrix and clip state since the last save call. It is an error to call sk_canvas_restore() more times than save and save_layer were called.

      • sk_canvas_draw_image_rect

        public static void sk_canvas_draw_image_rect(Skia.sk_canvas_t arg0,
                                             @Const
                                             Skia.sk_image_t arg1,

      • sk_canvas_draw_picture

        public static void sk_canvas_draw_picture(Skia.sk_canvas_t arg0,
                                          @Const
                                          Skia.sk_picture_t arg1,
                                          @Const
                                          Skia.sk_matrix_t arg2,
                                          @Const
                                          Skia.sk_paint_t arg3)
        Draw the picture into this canvas (replay the pciture's drawing commands).

        Parameters:
        sk_matrix_t* - If non-null, apply that matrix to the CTM when drawing this picture. This is logically equivalent to: save, concat, draw_picture, restore.

        sk_paint_t* - If non-null, draw the picture into a temporary buffer, and then apply the paint's alpha, colorfilter, imagefilter, and xfermode to that buffer as it is drawn to the canvas. This is logically equivalent to save_layer(paint), draw_picture, restore.

      • sk_canvas_clear

        public static void sk_canvas_clear(Skia.sk_canvas_t arg0,
                                   @Cast(value="sk_color_t")
                                   int arg1)
        Helper method for drawing a color in SRC mode, completely replacing all the pixels in the current clip with this color.

      • sk_canvas_discard

        public static void sk_canvas_discard(Skia.sk_canvas_t arg0)
        This makes the contents of the canvas undefined. Subsequent calls that require reading the canvas contents will produce undefined results. Examples include blending and readPixels. The actual implementation is backend- dependent and one legal implementation is to do nothing. Like clear(), this ignores the clip. This function should only be called if the caller intends to subsequently draw to the canvas. The canvas may do real work at discard() time in order to optimize performance on subsequent draws. Thus, if you call this and then never draw to the canvas subsequently you may pay a perfomance penalty.

      • sk_canvas_get_save_count

        public static int sk_canvas_get_save_count(Skia.sk_canvas_t arg0)
        Returns the number of matrix/clip states on the SkCanvas' private stack. This will equal # save() calls - # restore() calls + 1. The save count on a new canvas is 1.

      • sk_canvas_restore_to_count

        public static void sk_canvas_restore_to_count(Skia.sk_canvas_t arg0,
                                              int saveCount)
        Efficient way to pop any calls to sk_canvas_save() that happened after the save count reached saveCount. It is an error for saveCount to be greater than getSaveCount(). To pop all the way back to the initial matrix/clip context pass saveCount == 1.

      • sk_canvas_draw_color

        public static void sk_canvas_draw_color(Skia.sk_canvas_t ccanvas,
                                        @Cast(value="sk_color_t")
                                        int color,
                                        @Cast(value="sk_blendmode_t")
                                        int mode)

      • sk_canvas_draw_points

        public static void sk_canvas_draw_points(Skia.sk_canvas_t arg0,
                                         @Cast(value="sk_point_mode_t")
                                         int arg1,
                                         @Cast(value="size_t")
                                         long arg2,
                                         @Const
                                         Skia.sk_point_t arg3,
                                         @Const
                                         Skia.sk_paint_t arg4)
        Draw a series of points, interpreted based on the sk_point_mode_t mode. For all modes, the count parameter is interpreted as the total number of points. For LINES_SK_POINT_MODE mode, count/2 line segments are drawn. For POINTS_SK_POINT_MODE mode, each point is drawn centered at its coordinate, and its size is specified by the paint's stroke-width. It draws as a square, unless the paint's cap-type is round, in which the points are drawn as circles. For LINES_SK_POINT_MODE mode, each pair of points is drawn as a line segment, respecting the paint's settings for cap/join/width. For POLYGON_SK_POINT_MODE mode, the entire array is drawn as a series of connected line segments. Note that, while similar, LINES_SK_POINT_MODE and POLYGON_SK_POINT_MODE modes draw slightly differently than the equivalent path built with a series of moveto, lineto calls, in that the path will draw all of its contours at once, with no interactions if contours intersect each other (think XOR xfermode). sk_canvas_draw_paint always draws each element one at a time.

        Draws a single point with the specified paint

                                           Skia.sk_point_t arg3,
                                           @Const
                                           Skia.sk_paint_t paint)
        Draw the text, with each character/glyph origin specified by the pos[] array. The origin is interpreted by the Align setting in the paint.

        Parameters:
        text - The text to be drawn
        byteLength - The number of bytes to read from the text parameter
        pos - Array of positions, used to position each character
        paint - The paint used for the text (e.g. color, size, style)

      • sk_canvas_draw_text_on_path

        public static void sk_canvas_draw_text_on_path(Skia.sk_canvas_t arg0,
                                               @Cast(value="const char*")
                                               BytePointer text,
                                               @Cast(value="size_t")
                                               long byteLength,
                                               @Const
                                               Skia.sk_path_t path,
                                               float hOffset,
                                               float vOffset,
                                               @Const
                                               Skia.sk_paint_t paint)
        Draw the text, with origin at (x,y), using the specified paint, along the specified path. The paint's Align setting determins where along the path to start the text.

        Parameters:

        path - The path the text should follow for its baseline
        hOffset - The distance along the path to add to the text's starting position

        paint - The paint used for the text

      • sk_canvas_draw_bitmap

        public static void sk_canvas_draw_bitmap(Skia.sk_canvas_t ccanvas,
                                         @Const
                                         Skia.sk_bitmap_t bitmap,
                                         float left,
                                         float top,
                                         @Const
                                         Skia.sk_paint_t paint)
        Draw the specified bitmap, with its top/left corner at (x,y), using the specified paint, transformed by the current matrix. Note: if the paint contains a maskfilter that generates a mask which extends beyond the bitmap's original width/height, then the bitmap will be drawn as if it were in a Shader with CLAMP mode. Thus the color outside of the original width/height will be the edge color replicated.

        If a shader is present on the paint it will be ignored, except in the case where the bitmap is kAlpha_8_SkColorType. In that case, the color is generated by the shader.

        Parameters:
        bitmap - The bitmap to be drawn
        left - The position of the left side of the bitmap being drawn
        top - The position of the top side of the bitmap being drawn
        paint - The paint used to draw the bitmap, or NULL

      • sk_canvas_draw_bitmap_rect

        public static void sk_canvas_draw_bitmap_rect(Skia.sk_canvas_t ccanvas,
                                              @Const
                                              Skia.sk_bitmap_t bitmap,
                                              @Const
                                              Skia.sk_rect_t src,
                                              @Const
                                              Skia.sk_rect_t dst,
                                              @Const
                                              Skia.sk_paint_t paint)
        Draw the specified bitmap, scaling and translating so that it fills the specified dst rect. If the src rect is non-null, only that subset of the bitmap is transformed and drawn.
        Parameters:
        bitmap - The bitmap to be drawn
        src - Optional: specify the subset of the bitmap to be drawn
        dst - The destination rectangle where the scaled/translated bitmap will be drawn
        paint - The paint used to draw the bitmap, or NULL

      • sk_data_new_from_malloc

        public static Skia.sk_data_t sk_data_new_from_malloc(@Const
                                                     Pointer memory,
                                                     @Cast(value="size_t")
                                                     long length)
        Pass ownership of the given memory to a new sk_data_t, which will call free() when the refernce count of the data goes to zero. For example: size_t length = 1024; void* buffer = malloc(length); memset(buffer, 'X', length); sk_data_t* data = sk_data_new_from_malloc(buffer, length); This call must be balanced with a call to sk_data_unref().

        public static void sk_data_ref(@Const
                               Skia.sk_data_t arg0)
        Increment the reference count on the given sk_data_t. Must be balanced by a call to sk_data_unref().

      • sk_data_unref

        public static void sk_data_unref(@Const
                                 Skia.sk_data_t arg0)
        Decrement the reference count. If the reference count is 1 before the decrement, then release both the memory holding the sk_data_t and the memory it is managing. New sk_data_t are created with a reference count of 1.

      • sk_data_get_size

        @Cast(value="size_t")
public static long sk_data_get_size(@Const
                                                          Skia.sk_data_t arg0)
        Returns the number of bytes stored.

      • sk_data_get_data

        @Const
public static Pointer sk_data_get_data(@Const
                                              Skia.sk_data_t arg0)
        Returns the pointer to the data.

      • sk_data_new_from_file

        public static Skia.sk_data_t sk_data_new_from_file(@Cast(value="const char*")
                                                   BytePointer path)
        Create a new dataref the file with the specified path. If the file cannot be opened, this returns NULL.

      • sk_data_new_from_file

        public static Skia.sk_data_t sk_data_new_from_file(String path)

      • sk_data_new_from_stream

        public static Skia.sk_data_t sk_data_new_from_stream(Skia.sk_stream_t stream,
                                                     @Cast(value="size_t")
                                                     long length)
        Attempt to read size bytes into a SkData. If the read succeeds, return the data, else return NULL. Either way the stream's cursor may have been changed as a result of calling read().

      • sk_data_get_bytes

        @Cast(value="const uint8_t*")
public static BytePointer sk_data_get_bytes(@Const
                                                                          Skia.sk_data_t arg0)
        Like data(), returns a read-only ptr into the data, but in this case it is cast to uint8_t*, to make it easy to add an offset to it.

      • sk_matrix_map_vectors

        public static void sk_matrix_map_vectors(Skia.sk_matrix_t matrix,
                                         Skia.sk_point_t dst,
                                         Skia.sk_point_t src,
                                         int count)
        Apply this matrix to the array of vectors specified by src, and write the transformed vectors into the array of vectors specified by dst. This is similar to mapPoints, but ignores any translation in the matrix.
        Parameters:
        dst - Where the transformed coordinates are written. It must contain at least count entries
        src - The original coordinates that are to be transformed. It must contain at least count entries
        count - The number of vectors in src to read, and then transform into dst.

        public static void sk_path_quad_to(Skia.sk_path_t arg0,
                                   float x0,
                                   float y0,
                                   float x1,
                                   float y1)
        Add a quadratic bezier from the last point, approaching control point (x0,y0), and ending at (x1,y1). If no sk_path_move_to() call has been made for this contour, the first point is automatically set to (0,0).

      • sk_path_conic_to

        public static void sk_path_conic_to(Skia.sk_path_t arg0,
                                    float x0,
                                    float y0,
                                    float x1,
                                    float y1,
                                    float w)
        Add a conic curve from the last point, approaching control point (x0,y01), and ending at (x1,y1) with weight w. If no sk_path_move_to() call has been made for this contour, the first point is automatically set to (0,0).

                                    float x2,
                                    float y2)

      • sk_path_reset

        public static void sk_path_reset(Skia.sk_path_t cpath)
        Clear any lines and curves from the path, making it empty. This frees up internal storage associated with those segments. On Android, does not change fSourcePath.

      • sk_path_rewind

        public static void sk_path_rewind(Skia.sk_path_t cpath)
        Similar to sk_path_reset (), in that all lines and curves are removed from the path. However, any internal storage for those lines/curves is retained, making reuse of the path potentially faster. On Android, does not change fSourcePath.

      • sk_picture_recorder_end_recording

        public static Skia.sk_picture_t sk_picture_recorder_end_recording(Skia.sk_picture_recorder_t arg0)
        Signal that the caller is done recording. This invalidates the canvas returned by begin_recording. Ownership of the sk_picture_t is passed to the caller, who must call sk_picture_unref() when they are done using it. The returned picture is immutable.

      • sk_picture_unref

        public static void sk_picture_unref(Skia.sk_picture_t arg0)
        Decrement the reference count. If the reference count is 1 before the decrement, then release both the memory holding the sk_picture_t and any resouces it may be managing. New sk_picture_t are created with a reference count of 1.

        public static Skia.sk_shader_t sk_shader_new_linear_gradient(@Const
                                                             Skia.sk_point_t points,
                                                             @Cast(value="const sk_color_t*")
                                                             IntPointer colors,
                                                             @Const
                                                             FloatPointer colorPos,
                                                             int colorCount,
                                                             @Cast(value="sk_shader_tilemode_t")
                                                             int tileMode,
                                                             @Const
                                                             Skia.sk_matrix_t localMatrix)
        Returns a shader that generates a linear gradient between the two specified points.

        Parameters:
        points - The start and end points for the gradient.
        colors - The array[count] of colors, to be distributed between the two points
        colorPos - May be NULL. array[count] of SkScalars, or NULL, of the relative position of each corresponding color in the colors array. If this is NULL, the the colors are distributed evenly between the start and end point. If this is not null, the values must begin with 0, end with 1.0, and intermediate values must be strictly increasing.
        colorCount - Must be >=2. The number of colors (and pos if not NULL) entries.
        mode - The tiling mode

        public static Skia.sk_shader_t sk_shader_new_radial_gradient(@Const
                                                             Skia.sk_point_t center,

                                                             @Cast(value="const sk_color_t*")

                                                             @Const
                                                             Skia.sk_matrix_t localMatrix)
        Returns a shader that generates a radial gradient given the center and radius.

        Parameters:
        center - The center of the circle for this gradient
        radius - Must be positive. The radius of the circle for this gradient
        colors - The array[count] of colors, to be distributed between the center and edge of the circle
        colorPos - May be NULL. The array[count] of the relative position of each corresponding color in the colors array. If this is NULL, the the colors are distributed evenly between the center and edge of the circle. If this is not null, the values must begin with 0, end with 1.0, and intermediate values must be strictly increasing.
        count - Must be >= 2. The number of colors (and pos if not NULL) entries
        tileMode - The tiling mode
        localMatrix - May be NULL

                                                            Skia.sk_point_t center,
                                                            @Cast(value="const sk_color_t*")
                                                            IntPointer colors,
                                                            @Const
                                                            FloatPointer colorPos,
                                                            int colorCount,
                                                            @Const
                                                            Skia.sk_matrix_t localMatrix)
        Returns a shader that generates a sweep gradient given a center.

        Parameters:
        center - The coordinates of the center of the sweep
        colors - The array[count] of colors, to be distributed around the center.
        colorPos - May be NULL. The array[count] of the relative position of each corresponding color in the colors array. If this is NULL, the the colors are distributed evenly between the center and edge of the circle. If this is not null, the values must begin with 0, end with 1.0, and intermediate values must be strictly increasing.
        colorCount - Must be >= 2. The number of colors (and pos if not NULL) entries
        localMatrix - May be NULL

      • sk_shader_new_two_point_conical_gradient

        public static Skia.sk_shader_t sk_shader_new_two_point_conical_gradient(@Const
                                                                        Skia.sk_point_t start,
                                                                        float startRadius,
                                                                        @Const
                                                                        Skia.sk_point_t end,
                                                                        float endRadius,
                                                                        @Cast(value="const sk_color_t*")
                                                                        IntPointer colors,
                                                                        @Const
                                                                        FloatPointer colorPos,
                                                                        int colorCount,
                                                                        @Cast(value="sk_shader_tilemode_t")
                                                                        int tileMode,
                                                                        @Const
                                                                        Skia.sk_matrix_t localMatrix)
        Returns a shader that generates a conical gradient given two circles, or returns NULL if the inputs are invalid. The gradient interprets the two circles according to the following HTML spec. http://dev.w3.org/html5/2dcontext/#dom-context-2d-createradialgradient

        Returns a shader that generates a sweep gradient given a center.

        Parameters:
        start, - startRadius Defines the first circle.
        end, - endRadius Defines the first circle.
        colors - The array[count] of colors, to be distributed between the two circles.
        colorPos - May be NULL. The array[count] of the relative position of each corresponding color in the colors array. If this is NULL, the the colors are distributed evenly between the two circles. If this is not null, the values must begin with 0, end with 1.0, and intermediate values must be strictly increasing.
        colorCount - Must be >= 2. The number of colors (and pos if not NULL) entries
        tileMode - The tiling mode
        localMatrix - May be NULL

        public static Skia.sk_surface_t sk_surface_new_raster(@Const
                                                      Skia.sk_imageinfo_t arg0,
                                                      @Const
                                                      Skia.sk_surfaceprops_t arg1)
        Return a new surface, with the memory for the pixels automatically allocated. If the requested surface cannot be created, or the request is not a supported configuration, NULL will be returned.

        Parameters:
        sk_imageinfo_t* - Specify the width, height, color type, and alpha type for the surface.

        sk_surfaceprops_t* - If not NULL, specify additional non-default properties of the surface.

      • sk_surface_new_raster_direct

        public static Skia.sk_surface_t sk_surface_new_raster_direct(@Const
                                                             Skia.sk_imageinfo_t arg0,
                                                             Pointer pixels,
                                                             @Cast(value="size_t")
                                                             long rowBytes,
                                                             @Const
                                                             Skia.sk_surfaceprops_t props)
        Create a new surface which will draw into the specified pixels with the specified rowbytes. If the requested surface cannot be created, or the request is not a supported configuration, NULL will be returned.

        Parameters:
        sk_imageinfo_t* - Specify the width, height, color type, and alpha type for the surface.
        void* - pixels Specify the location in memory where the destination pixels are. This memory must outlast this surface.
        size_t - rowBytes Specify the difference, in bytes, between each adjacent row. Should be at least (width * sizeof(one pixel)).
        sk_surfaceprops_t* - If not NULL, specify additional non-default properties of the surface.
